<h3>New Pet Abilities</h3>
<p>Your pet has just gained a significant boost in HP and natural regeneration
rates.&nbsp; You will now find it much easier to use the pet to solo.&nbsp; In
my opinion, 34 - 39 is the largest relative increase in the power of pets, but
there's only good things ahead.&nbsp; 44 - 49 is another big boost in HP and
then you'll hit start on the Vocerate pets at 51</p>

<h3>Summon Ring of Flight</h3>
<p>You've waited a long time for this compared to other classes, but now you can
cast levitate.&nbsp; Well, technically you can summon a ring that has 2 charges
of levitate on it.&nbsp; The ring has 3 benefits over the Levitate spell of
other classes: 1) You can hand this to others so that they can levitate
themselves when they need it, 2) It does not require bat wings, 3) It casts
instantly (even if you're falling).&nbsp; You need not wear the ring to use
it.&nbsp; Just target it and right click.&nbsp; You'll find yourself being
levitated frequently after handing these rings to people.&nbsp; (Many people
assume the ring automatically targets them, but it may be cast on any
target...and since you just traded the ring, you
are the target).</p>

<h3>Summon Companion</h3>
<p>This spell will bring your pet to your position from anywhere in the zone as
long as your pet is minding its own business.&nbsp; If your pet is fighting a
mob or on the hate list of a mob, this spell fails.&nbsp; You must target your
pet before casting it.&nbsp; Many zones have poor pathing.&nbsp; No doubt,
you've been in places where your pet seems to find the long way around -- or
even gets completely lost.&nbsp; This spell can be used to avoid pathing
hassles.&nbsp; Park your pet, move to where you want to go and then summon your
pet to you!</p>

<p>Your pet isn't real bright, but it is very loyal.&nbsp; If you told your pet
to guard a location, and then summon it to a different location, it will
immediately try to get back to the guard point.&nbsp; Be ready to instantly
issue a new guard command -- or even better, leave your pet in sit or stand mode
rather than guard.</p>

<h3>Dagger of Symbols</h3>
<p>This new summoned item is a small dagger with +5 to save disease, save magic
and save poison.&nbsp; Since these are daggers, they can be equipped in a weapon
hand or the range slot.&nbsp; As a caster, you can hold two of these (one in
primary and one in range).&nbsp; Melee classes and your pet can hold 3.</p>

